<title>Security Policy</title>
<indexterm><primary>Security Policy</primary></indexterm>

<para><anchor xml:id="_md_public_2glpi_2_s_e_c_u_r_i_t_y_1autotoc_md3053"/> <emphasis role="bold">⚠️ Please never use standard issues to report security problems; vulnerabilities are published once a fix release is available. ⚠️</emphasis></para>
<section xml:id="_md_public_2glpi_2_s_e_c_u_r_i_t_y_1autotoc_md3054">
<title><title>Reporting a Vulnerability</title></title>

<para>If you found a security issue, please contact us by:</para>

<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>a mail to [glpi-security AT ow2.org]</para>
</listitem><listitem>
<para>open an advisory on <link xlink:href="https://github.com/glpi-project/glpi/security/advisories/new">github</link></para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>

<para>You should provide us all details about the issue and the way to reproduce it. You may also provide a script that can be used to check the issue exists.</para>

<para>Once the report will be handled, and if the issue is not yet fixed (or in progress) we&apos;ll add it to the GitHub security tab, and add you as observer. Meanwhile, you will reserve a CVE for the issue.</para>

<para>Thank you for improving the security of glpi.</para>
</section>
